 Three people were killed in a car crash and three others injured in Bada Romo village in Ganjuwa LGA of Bauchi State. A Road Traffic Crash (RTC) of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) made available to journalists on revealed that the accident occurred on Saturday, February 25, 2023, involving two vehicles, a Dangote truck with registration number, ABS 620XA, and a Ford Focus car with registration number, AG999JRE. The report noted that the probable cause of the crash was wrong overtaking which led to a head-on-collision.  